When NodeJS added support for ESM, they needed a way to know whether your source code was ESM or CJS.

They gave two ways to control it:

File extensions:

- .cjs = CommonJS
- .mjs = ESM
- .js = ambigous

If you use .js as your file extension, they look for the nearest parent package.json file that has a "type" field:

- "type": "commonjs" # CommonJS
- "type": "module" # ESM

If they make it to the root of your filesystem without finding this field, there are a few more heuristics, but you're likely to default to CommonJS.
